{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuProtocol"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuProtocol\/remove(position:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GIO","externalID":"s:3GIO12MenuProtocolPAAE6remove8positionySi_tF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"remove","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"position","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"title":"remove(position:)","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Removes an item from the menu."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"remove","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"position"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"position"},{"type":"text","text":" gives the index of the item to remove."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is an error if position is not in range the range from 0 to one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"less than the number of items in the menu."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is not possible to remove items by identity since items are added"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the menu simply by copying their links and attributes (ie:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"identity of the item itself is not preserved).","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/menuprotocol\/remove(position:)"]}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MenuProtocol/remove(position:)":{"title":"remove(position:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"remove","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"position","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuProtocol\/remove(position:)","abstract":[{"text":"Removes an item from the menu.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/menuprotocol\/remove(position:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MenuItem":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuItem","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MenuItem","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MenuItem","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MenuItem","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/menuitem","abstract":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuItem","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is an opaque structure type.  You must access it using the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions below."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MenuProtocol":{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenu"},{"type":"text","text":" is a simple implementation of [class"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You populate a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GMenu","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" by adding [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuItem","isActive":true},{"text":"] instances to it.","type":"text"}],"title":"MenuProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MenuProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MenuProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuProtocol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/menuprotocol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MenuModel":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MenuModel"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/menumodel","title":"MenuModel","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MenuModel","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":" represents the contents of a menu — an ordered list of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"menu items. The items are associated with actions, which can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"activated through them. Items can be grouped in sections, and may","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have submenus associated with them. Both items and sections usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"have some representation data, such as labels or icons. The type of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the associated action (ie whether it is stateful, and what kind of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state it has) can influence the representation of the item."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}